                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus of
                                Antioch</persName> and <persName
                                    ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3729">Anonymi 3729</persName> exchanged letters 
                            on questions of whether or not there would be sufficient ordained clergy to adminster
                            the Lord's Supper and baptism to the women. <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus of
                                Antioch</persName> states that deaconnesses may administer baptism to women and male 
                            presbyters or deacons may administer the Lord's Supper.
